description: Retrieves a list of all inference schedulers currently available for your account.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: An opaque pagination token indicating where to continue the listing of inference schedulers.

nested_items.name: InferenceSchedulerSummaries
nested_items.description: Provides information about the specified inference scheduler, including data upload frequency, model name and ARN, and status.

nested_items.name: ModelName
nested_items.description: The name of the machine learning model used for the inference scheduler.

nested_items.name: ModelArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the machine learning model used by the inference scheduler.

nested_items.name: InferenceSchedulerName
nested_items.description: The name of the inference scheduler.

nested_items.name: InferenceSchedulerArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the inference scheduler.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: Indicates the status of the inference scheduler.

nested_items.name: DataDelayOffsetInMinutes
nested_items.description: A period of time (in minutes) by which inference on the data is delayed after the data starts. For instance, if an offset delay time of five minutes was selected, inference will not begin on the data until the first data measurement after the five minute mark. For example, if five minutes is selected, the inference scheduler will wake up at the configured frequency with the additional five minute delay time to check the customer S3 bucket. The customer can upload data at the same frequency and they don't need to stop and restart the scheduler when uploading new data.

nested_items.name: DataUploadFrequency
nested_items.description: How often data is uploaded to the source S3 bucket for the input data. This value is the length of time between data uploads. For instance, if you select 5 minutes, Amazon Lookout for Equipment will upload the real-time data to the source bucket once every 5 minutes. This frequency also determines how often Amazon Lookout for Equipment starts a scheduled inference on your data. In this example, it starts once every 5 minutes.

nested_items.name: LatestInferenceResult
nested_items.description: Indicates whether the latest execution for the inference scheduler was Anomalous (anomalous events found) or Normal (no anomalous events found).
